From 406e35eef106ddea6e83f9f32912f5ac4e41989e Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: yichongt <yichong.tang@intel.com>
Date: Thu, 28 May 2026 14:15:09 +0800
Subject: [PATCH 1/2] [Feat] Restructure the pi05 + RTC eval pipeline for the
 Aloha MuJoCo simulator. (#3)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

* [Refactor] aloha eval pipeline: persistent threads, render decoupling, viz subprocess

Restructure the pi05 + RTC eval pipeline so it can run multiple episodes back-to-back
without thread restarts and without the local desktop GUI starving the action loop:

- Make get_actions and actor_control persistent across episodes; use episode_end_event
  for episode-boundary signaling and keep the EGL/GL context bound to a single thread
  for the whole run.
- Add keyboard control (Space pause/resume, r toggle RTC), per-episode pause
  state, and BooleanOptional --rtc-enabled flag.
- MujocoAlohaRobot: dedicated render thread with its own EGL context via mujoco.Renderer
  and a _physics_lock; 24fps angle-camera viz + on-demand 4-camera inference renders;
  reuse env across episodes; fix multi-episode reset (do not call physics.reset_context()
  a second time, which was wiping cube pose back to XML default).
- Force MUJOCO_GL=egl so rendering goes through DRM/iGPU instead of GLFW/X11.
- Move visualization into a child process via shared memory + cv2.imshow, freeing the
  main GIL so it does not contend with X11 / GUI events under a local desktop.
- Save trajectory data as .npz/.json alongside the existing plot.
- Switch base deps to Python 3.12 and opencv-python (GUI build) needed by the cv2
  child-process viewer.

* Fix Python version mismatch in CI workflows (3.10 → 3.12)
